 @REFRESHSCOPE -- HOW IT WORKS
================================================================================
  FLOW:
  -----
  ConfigMap updated (order.max-items: 500)
          |
          v
  Config Watcher detects change
          |
          v
  POST /actuator/refresh called on pod
          |
          v
  RefreshScope destroys all @RefreshScope beans (clears CGLIB proxy cache)
          |
          v
  On next method call --> bean re-created with fresh @Value from Environment
          |
          v
  OrderController (new) --> maxItems = 500  [no restart needed]
 
  WHAT HAPPENS INTERNALLY:
  ------------------------
  - Spring wraps every @RefreshScope bean in a CGLIB proxy
  - On /actuator/refresh --> scope clears its internal bean cache
  - On the next method call through the proxy --> bean is re-created
  - All @Value fields are re-read from the updated Environment
  - No pod restart, no connection drop
 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 BASIC USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  @RestController
  @RefreshScope        // entire controller re-created on refresh
  public class OrderController {
      @Value("${order.max-items:100}")
      private int maxItems;
      @Value("${order.payment-timeout:30s}")
      private String paymentTimeout;
      @GetMapping("/config")
      public Map<String, Object> config() {
          return Map.of("maxItems", maxItems, "timeout", paymentTimeout);
      }
  }
 
