================================================================================
 
  Ansible provisions HashiCorp Vault (Pattern D)
       +
  Spring Cloud Vault
       +
  @RefreshScope
       +
  Spring Cloud Kubernetes Config Watcher
       |
       v
  Secrets fetched at startup, never written to disk,
  rotate without restarting pods, full audit trail.
 
================================================================================
 PROPERTY LOADING PRIORITY IN SPRING BOOT
================================================================================
  (Highest priority first -- later sources override earlier ones)
  1.  Command line args           --server.port=9090
  2.  SPRING_APPLICATION_JSON    env var (inline JSON)
  3.  OS Environment variables    SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD
  4.  application-{profile}.yml  (profile-specific)
  5.  application.yml            (default)
  6.  @ConfigurationProperties   bound classes
  7.  Config Server / ConfigMap  (Spring Cloud sources)
  8.  HashiCorp Vault            (Spring Cloud Vault -- lowest, loaded first)
 
  Note: Spring Cloud external sources (Vault, ConfigMap) are loaded in
  bootstrap phase BEFORE application.yml, so they appear lower in the
  override chain -- they can be overridden by local application.yml
  if needed. 
 
